"title": "8770: idolatry, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8770",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The NT world included many religions which promoted the worship of idols. Idolatry was thus of continuing importance to NT writers, especially Paul.</p>\n<h2>Idolatry in the Gentile world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:16\">ACT 17:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:11-Acts14:13\">ACT 14:11–14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:22-Acts17:23\">ACT 17:22–17:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:24\">ACT 19:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:5\">1CO 8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:8\">GAL 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Criticism of idolatry</h2>\n<h3>Idolatry leads to other sinful behaviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:24\">ROM 1:24</a></strong> <em>Verses 22 and 24–25 show the link between idolatry and immoral conduct.</em></p>\n<h3>Idolatry is an offence against the doctrine of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:20\">ROM 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24-Acts17:29\">ACT 17:24–17:29</a></p>\n<h3>Idols are futile and degrading</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:22-Rom1:23\">ROM 1:22–1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:4\">1CO 8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:19\">1CO 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:2\">1CO 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatrous worship of human beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:22\">ACT 12:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:24-Luke20:25\">LUK 20:24–20:25</a> <em>Jesus Christ opposes the hypocrisy which objected to Roman coinage as idolatrous on the grounds that the emperor's head infringed the Ten Commandments</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:6\">ACT 28:6</a></p>\n<h3>Demonic powers are involved with idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:20\">1CO 10:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:20\">REV 9:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:4\">REV 13:4</a></p>\n<h3>Food sacrificed to idols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:20\">ACT 15:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:2-Rom14:3\">ROM 14:2–14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:6\">ROM 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:4-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:4–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:14-1Cor10:31\">1CO 10:14–10:31</a></p>\n<h3>Encounters with idolatrous practice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:28\">ACT 19:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:11-Acts14:18\">ACT 14:11–14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:18-Acts17:31\">ACT 17:18–17:31</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual idolatry</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:21\">1JN 5:21</a></strong> <em>“idols” here may well refer to a wide range of God-substitutes.</em></p>\n<h2>The temptations of Jesus Christ present three main kinds of spiritual idolatry</h2>\n<h3>Possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:3\">MAT 4:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:3\">LUK 4:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24\">MAT 6:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:13\">LUK 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:23\">LUK 18:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:19\">PHP 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:10</a></p>\n<h3>Prestige and self-esteem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:6\">MAT 4:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:9\">LUK 4:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:8\">LUK 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:29\">LUK 10:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:11-Luke18:12\">LUK 18:11–18:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:21\">LUK 18:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:19\">ROM 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:8-Matt4:9\">MAT 4:8–4:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:6-Luke4:7\">LUK 4:6–4:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:54-Luke9:55\">LUK 9:54–9:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:39\">LUK 23:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:10-John18:11\">JHN 18:10–18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:10\">JHN 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6\">PHP 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:6\">JAS 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:10\">JAS 4:10</a></p>",
